  "stem": "<p>A right triangle has one leg of length <math><mn>8</mn></math>, another leg of length <math><mi>b</mi></math>, and a hypotenuse of length <math><mn>19</mn></math>. Which of the following gives the value of <math><mi>b</mi></math>?</p>",
  "answerOptions": [
    {
      "id": "a",
      "content": "<p><math><mn>19</mn><mo>-</mo><mn>8</mn></math></p>"
    },
    {
      "id": "b",
      "content": "<p><math><msqrt><msup><mn>19</mn><mn>2</mn></msup><mo>-</mo><msup><mn>8</mn><mn>2</mn></msup></msqrt></math></p>"
    },
    {
      "id": "c",
      "content": "<p><math><msqrt><msup><mn>19</mn><mn>2</mn></msup><mo>+</mo><msup><mn>8</mn><mn>2</mn></msup></msqrt></math></p>"
    },
    {
      "id": "d",
      "content": "<p><math><msup><mn>19</mn><mn>2</mn></msup><mo>-</mo><msup><mn>8</mn><mn>2</mn></msup></math></p>"
    }
  ],
  "keys": [
    "b"
  ],
  "rationale": "<p>Choice B is correct. By the Pythagorean theorem, 8\u00b2 + b\u00b2 = 19\u00b2, so b\u00b2 = 19\u00b2 - 8\u00b2 and b = \u221a(19\u00b2 - 8\u00b2).</p><p>Choice A treats sides like lengths in a sum. Choice C would apply if b were the hypotenuse. Choice D omits the square root.</p>",
